<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="42" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[140,1161,1227,1681]" pageId="13" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[179,289,1227,1251]" pageId="13" pageNumber="42">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(female). The unforked vein 3 places this in the group of species previously assigned to the separate genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Sccmitz. Schmitz (1949)" authorityName="Sccmitz. Schmitz" authorityYear="1949" box="[469,826,1258,1282]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Citrago" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[469,552,1258,1281]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="42">Citrago</emphasis>
Sccmitz. 
<bibRefCitation author="Schmitz" box="[658,826,1258,1282]" firstAuthor="Schmitz" pageId="13" pageNumber="42" pagination="193 - 240" refId="ref4766" refString="SCHMITZ H. 1949. Phoridae. In: Lindner E (ed.), Die Fliegen der palaearktischen Region 4 (33) (Lieferung 160): 193 - 240. Stuttgart, E. Schweizerbart'sche Verlagsbuchhandlung." type="journal article" year="1949">Schmitz (1949)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="DELAGE A &amp; LAURAIRE M-C." box="[837,1115,1258,1282]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin des Recherches Agronomiques de Gembloux" pageId="13" pageNumber="42" pagination="450 - 458" part="5" refId="ref4619" refString="DELAGE A. &amp; LAURAIRE M-C. 1970. Trois nouvelles especes de Phoridae (Dipteres, Brachyceres, Cyclorrhaphes), trouvees a Peyresq (Alpes de Provence). Bulletin des Recherches Agronomiques de Gembloux 5: 450 - 458." title="Trois nouvelles especes de Phoridae (Dipteres, Brachyceres, Cyclorrhaphes), trouvees a Peyresq (Alpes de Provence)" type="journal article" year="1970">Delage &amp; Lauraire (1970)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Disney" box="[140,295,1289,1313]" firstAuthor="Disney" pageId="13" pageNumber="42" pagination="135 - 139" refId="ref4617" refString="DISNEY R. H. L. 1994. A new species of Triphleba (Diptera: Phoridae) from France and the subfamily assignment of this genus. Giornale Italiano di Entomologia 6: 135 - 139 (1992)." type="journal article" year="1994">Disney (1994)</bibRefCitation>
cover the males of the European species. Most are only known from the males. The costal index being clearly less than 0.50 immediately distinguishes this species from the rest of this species group.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[140,1161,1227,1681]" pageId="13" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[179,262,1381,1405]" pageId="13" pageNumber="42">Female</emphasis>
. Frons as 
<figureCitation box="[372,451,1380,1405]" captionStart="Figs 66–71" captionStartId="14.[140,177,1620,1639]" captionTargetBox="[146,1149,171,1592]" captionTargetId="figure-5@14.[146,652,672,1106]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figs 66–71. Triphleba brevicostalis female. 66 - frons; 67 - palps and proboscis; 68 - side of thorax; 69, abdominal tergites 5 and 6; 70 – sternum 7; 71 – furca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252479" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252479/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="42">Fig. 66</figureCitation>
. Palps and proboscis as 
<figureCitation box="[708,787,1380,1405]" captionStart="Figs 66–71" captionStartId="14.[140,177,1620,1639]" captionTargetBox="[146,1149,171,1592]" captionTargetId="figure-5@14.[146,652,672,1106]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figs 66–71. Triphleba brevicostalis female. 66 - frons; 67 - palps and proboscis; 68 - side of thorax; 69, abdominal tergites 5 and 6; 70 – sternum 7; 71 – furca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252479" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252479/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="42">Fig. 67</figureCitation>
. Postpedicels dark brown and their lengths and breadths subequal (at about 
<quantity box="[570,669,1411,1435]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="13" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="0.11">0.11 mm</quantity>
). Side of thorax as 
<figureCitation box="[876,955,1411,1435]" captionStart="Figs 66–71" captionStartId="14.[140,177,1620,1639]" captionTargetBox="[146,1149,171,1592]" captionTargetId="figure-5@14.[146,652,672,1106]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figs 66–71. Triphleba brevicostalis female. 66 - frons; 67 - palps and proboscis; 68 - side of thorax; 69, abdominal tergites 5 and 6; 70 – sternum 7; 71 – furca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252479" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252479/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="42">Fig. 68</figureCitation>
. Scutellum with an anterior pair of minute hairs and a posterior pair of long bristles. Abdominal tergites brown with small hairs (
<figureCitation box="[268,347,1473,1497]" captionStart="Figs 66–71" captionStartId="14.[140,177,1620,1639]" captionTargetBox="[146,1149,171,1592]" captionTargetId="figure-5@14.[146,652,672,1106]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figs 66–71. Triphleba brevicostalis female. 66 - frons; 67 - palps and proboscis; 68 - side of thorax; 69, abdominal tergites 5 and 6; 70 – sternum 7; 71 – furca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252479" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252479/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="42">Fig. 69</figureCitation>
). Venter brown with hairs at rear of segment 6. Sternite 7 is seemingly absent (
<figureCitation box="[148,230,1503,1527]" captionStart="Figs 66–71" captionStartId="14.[140,177,1620,1639]" captionTargetBox="[146,1149,171,1592]" captionTargetId="figure-5@14.[146,652,672,1106]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figs 66–71. Triphleba brevicostalis female. 66 - frons; 67 - palps and proboscis; 68 - side of thorax; 69, abdominal tergites 5 and 6; 70 – sternum 7; 71 – furca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252479" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252479/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="42">Fig. 70</figureCitation>
). Furca as 
<figureCitation box="[349,429,1503,1527]" captionStart="Figs 66–71" captionStartId="14.[140,177,1620,1639]" captionTargetBox="[146,1149,171,1592]" captionTargetId="figure-5@14.[146,652,672,1106]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figs 66–71. Triphleba brevicostalis female. 66 - frons; 67 - palps and proboscis; 68 - side of thorax; 69, abdominal tergites 5 and 6; 70 – sternum 7; 71 – furca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252479" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252479/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="42">Fig. 71</figureCitation>
. Sternum 8 and cerci as 
<figureCitation box="[699,779,1503,1527]" captionStart="Figs 72–76" captionStartId="15.[140,177,1004,1023]" captionTargetBox="[146,1147,171,974]" captionTargetId="figure-8@15.[640,1146,412,712]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 72–76. Triphleba brevicostalis female. 72 – sternum 8 and cerci; 73 – front leg; 74 – mid tibia; 75 – hind femur and tibia; 76 – wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252483" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252483/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="42">Fig. 72</figureCitation>
. The legs pale brown to yellowish. Front legs as 
<figureCitation box="[290,371,1534,1558]" captionStart="Figs 72–76" captionStartId="15.[140,177,1004,1023]" captionTargetBox="[146,1147,171,974]" captionTargetId="figure-8@15.[640,1146,412,712]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 72–76. Triphleba brevicostalis female. 72 – sternum 8 and cerci; 73 – front leg; 74 – mid tibia; 75 – hind femur and tibia; 76 – wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252483" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252483/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="42">Fig. 73</figureCitation>
, the tibia lacking an anterodorsal bristle. Mid tibia as 
<figureCitation box="[971,1051,1534,1558]" captionStart="Figs 72–76" captionStartId="15.[140,177,1004,1023]" captionTargetBox="[146,1147,171,974]" captionTargetId="figure-8@15.[640,1146,412,712]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 72–76. Triphleba brevicostalis female. 72 – sternum 8 and cerci; 73 – front leg; 74 – mid tibia; 75 – hind femur and tibia; 76 – wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252483" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252483/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="42">Fig. 74</figureCitation>
, with one anterodorsal and 2 dorsal bristles. Hind femur and tibia as 
<figureCitation box="[769,847,1564,1589]" captionStart="Figs 72–76" captionStartId="15.[140,177,1004,1023]" captionTargetBox="[146,1147,171,974]" captionTargetId="figure-8@15.[640,1146,412,712]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 72–76. Triphleba brevicostalis female. 72 – sternum 8 and cerci; 73 – front leg; 74 – mid tibia; 75 – hind femur and tibia; 76 – wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252483" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252483/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="42">Fig. 75</figureCitation>
, the tibia with 1 anterodorsal bristle. The pale wing (
<figureCitation box="[388,465,1595,1619]" captionStart="Figs 72–76" captionStartId="15.[140,177,1004,1023]" captionTargetBox="[146,1147,171,974]" captionTargetId="figure-8@15.[640,1146,412,712]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 72–76. Triphleba brevicostalis female. 72 – sternum 8 and cerci; 73 – front leg; 74 – mid tibia; 75 – hind femur and tibia; 76 – wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252483" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252483/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="42">Fig. 76</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity box="[480,574,1595,1619]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="13" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="1.7">1.70 mm</quantity>
long and with the costal index 0.44 and vein 3 lacking the anterior fork (vein 2) and costal section 1 is only slightly longer than 2 (1.05: 1). Vein 7 not discernible. Halrtere brown (
<figureCitation box="[447,527,1657,1681]" captionStart="Figs 66–71" captionStartId="14.[140,177,1620,1639]" captionTargetBox="[146,1149,171,1592]" captionTargetId="figure-5@14.[146,652,672,1106]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figs 66–71. Triphleba brevicostalis female. 66 - frons; 67 - palps and proboscis; 68 - side of thorax; 69, abdominal tergites 5 and 6; 70 – sternum 7; 71 – furca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252479" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252479/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="42">Fig. 68</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
